    // "A" and "B" each appear twice (a full 1-100000 cycle, then a second one
    // years later) before C-G each appear once (so far - this data set ends at
    // CM1135-322/Dec 1947, still inside the first G cycle). A bare letter+number
    // like "A50000" is genuinely ambiguous between generations - it is NOT
    // linearized into one shared number space the way CM1132's blocks are.
    // lookupCertificateNumber() returns every record whose segment contains the
    // number; an optional "YYYY-" prefix narrows to the record(s) covering that
    // year.
